values: I have so many thoughts that I want to let people in on, but at the same time I hate people knowing everything about me. Although I don't think the entries in this journal show the real me too well. That's sad. Oh well. So my life is kinda good. I love my daughter with all of my heart and she brings so much happiness to my life. Without her, I'd probably either be really depressed or partying it and not giving a shit about the world. And both paths are pretty dark in my opinion. So, I'm very thankful for her being with me, no matter how hard it gets at times. Other aspects of my life could be better, I guess. Some people would think that I have it made: hardworking fiance, beautiful daughter, 3brm town house, stay at home mom. But life isn't always as good as it seems. My relationship with my fiance has always been really crazy. We love to fight, A LOT. I always see us being together, but always fighting. And I just hate to think that we'll forever be battling with one another. And I know that there is absolutely nothing we can do. We're too stubborn to make any kind of changes. We are two  very opinionated and different people. We can never stay mad at each other for too long though, I think that's what shows that we love and care for each other. If I didn't care about him, I would have just told him to go fuck himself a long time ago, because he is just so damn hard to deal with. I can probably write a novel about all the disagreements and arguments that we have, so I'm not even going to begin talking about that. I've went through an enormous range of emotions in this relationship, I don't think I've been through as much in my whole life as I have with him. Ahhh, I have so much more to say but not enough words in the dictionary to explain it all, seriously. I'll just leave it at that for now...

KATELYN was born on September 16th at 2:12pm. She weighed 9lbs 12oz and was 21 and three fourths inches long. She's a huge baby, and getting bigger by the hour!!! I was in labor for 12 long hours and I'm so happy she's finally here. Now I get to hold her and love her in my arms, not just my belly! She's 3 weeks and 1 day old today.

Wow, well it's been a while since I last wrote in here! I'm already 3 and half months pregnant, and my belly is growing like crazy. Monday I'm going to my first big doctors appt. Hopefully everything turns out okay though!

HELL YEAH! I just came back from my second interview, I got the job & I start tuesday!!! I'm excited that I finally got something in this hell hole of a town. It's not exactly what I want to be doing but it'll do for now. I won't be there for any longer than 7 months, because of the baby coming. I'll be working at Dillard's in the mall, it's one of the most expensive stores there, and I think the nicest. I'll be in the Juniors department, and they have the greatest shit there. I'll be their best customer. This should be an easy enough job, because it's not some stupid little cheap store where all the crack whores shop at, although this is Palmdale. So, we'll see how it goes, hopefully there won't be too many more people there that I hate. There is only one so far, but thankfully not in my department. Damn Bitch!!! Oh well, life goes on, but now with more money in my pocket! So, hell yeah!!!

Damn, Tassia and I got down tonight! We were dancin' like crazy, trying to take out some of that aggression from the stupid little bitches at Schooners. Ha, too fucken bad for them, the'll never be able to go there again, hahaha! Other than that, it was a shit load of fun. My body is hurtin' like a mother fucker!
Merry (late) X-Mas and have a Fantastic New Year too!

Matt's 21st b-day was funny as hell
Ha ha ...

Well, today's Matt's Birthday and he's sick as hell. We were supposed to go out tonight, but his ass just had to get sick. It was a pretty good birthday for him, other than that though. Tasha and I surprised him last night, when he got off work. We decided to go all out for him. So, we decorated the room, and bought balloons and confetti, wrapped up all his gifts. And we invited some of his cousins to come over, and surprised him in the room, with the lights off. He was pretty surprised. I'm glad we did that for him, because I guess he has never really had a good birthday before. He's snoring away right now though, damn, turned 21 and he's not even drinking tonight. But, tomorrow we're going to Schooners to celebrate. I'll be working for most of the night, but I'm sure we'll get to dance together too. His friends are going to be there, so he'll have some fun. It's supposed to be the busiest night of the year, because it's the day before Thanksgiving. Anyways, now Matt can buy us all alcohol! HaHaHa
